				\begin{document}$$ E^{{ - \Updelta C_{\text{t}} }} $$\end{document} where E is the reaction efficiency and then normalised by division with the normalising factor, calculated in the same way either singly (18s rRNA, wheat experiments and barley entrainment experiment) or as a geometric mean (18s rRNA and actin mRNA, barley 24 h experiments; Vandesompele et al. 2002) to control for fluctuations in cDNA synthesis efficiency. PCR primers used are listed in Online Resource 1.
